  "text": "As discussed in the section above, we have got the spatial continuous f values for the Sanjiang Plain but we used a regional mean f value to conduct analysis just because the spatial f values in the paddy expansion areas include both the information of the rain-fed farmland and paddy field during the study period. However, there were spatial differences for f due to different geographic conditions, such as elevation, soil moisture, and so on [CITATION_1] , resulting in spatial variations in the local surface temperature responses. Therefore, we used the spatial continuous f values which involved the LUC information in the Sanjiang Plain to discuss the uncertainties of ∆T s at the pixel level.",
